    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>BRITISH JOB CUTS ANNOUNCED</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Andrew Ross Sorkin</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Great Universal Stores PLC, Britain, in cost-cutting move, says it will merge its home shopping unit with its catalog chain unit; says action will result in elimination of 800 jobs (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Britain's largest mail-order company, Great Universal Stores P.L.C., announced it would merge its home shopping unit with its catalog chain unit, Argos. The move is meant to cut costs and will result in the elimination of 800 jobs. Great Universal Stores is hoping to increase sales by using the Argos brand, which has a retail presence throughout Britain.</p>
        <p>Andrew Ross Sorkin</p>
      </block>
